cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with still image super-resolution using deep learning-based approaches. Additionally, the use of lossless pooling convolutional networks suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The incorporation of self-replicas of the input image may also suggest that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks and extensive evaluations may suggest that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
